estring is a set of erlang string functions

supported functions:

begins_with(String, SubString)
    returns true if String begins with SubString
ends_with(String, SubString)
    returns true if String ends with SubString
contains(String, SubString)
    returns true if String contains SubString
edit_distance(String1, String2)
    returns the damerau-levenshtein edit distance between String1 and String2
similarity(String, TargetString)
    returns a case-insensitive score representing how similar String is to
    TargetString based on the edit distance and the length of TargetString
is_integer(String)
    returns true if String is is a string representation of an integer,
    e.g. "35"

examples:

1> estring:begins_with("fancy pants", "fancy").
true
2> estring:ends_with("fancy pants", "pants").
true
3> estring:contains("los angeles", "angel").  
true
4> estring:edit_distance("cars", "bats").
2
5> estring:edit_distance("receive", "recieve").
1
6> estring:similarity("epsn sporrts", "espn sports").
0.8181818181818182
7> estring:similarity("edit distance", "Edit Distance").            
1.0
8> estring:is_integer("35").
true
9> estring:is_integer("35.4").
false
